1. shouldn't the class names be "org.trafodion...." instead of "com.trafodion..."
2. In the pre-apache product, we had 2 levels of security. a) component privileges that controlled who can upload jar or create library or create procedure etc. b) execute privilege on these system SPJs. 
3. It is not clear to me if we need to sandbox the SPJs in user specific directories. In the pre-apache product we had tried user and role specific folders and it was a nightmare to share and manage the SPJs by different admin users and we had reverted back to a single base folder. With the combination of the component privileges and SQL privileges we can control security.
Is this ready to commit now?

This code originally was written for a different security implementation that included OpenSSL files in the source tree.  However, this code was subsequently rewritten that removed OpenSSL dependency. Therefore, Trafodion no longer has a source dependency with OpenSSL.  When changes were made to remove the OpenSSL dependency, the LICENSE file should have been removed but was not.  So, removing this file is a code cleanup operation.
